    <sect1 id="introduction" status="review">
        <title>Introduction</title>
        <para>The &app; is a graphical frontend to the <application>APT</application> package
            management system for the K Desktop Environment (KDE). Modeled along the lines of
                <application>Synaptic</application>, a graphical interface developed for the GNOME
            Desktop Environment, &appshort; provides an easy-to-use and familiar interface via
            which users can perform software management operations.</para>
        <para>&appshort; can be started from the K menu system or the command line. In order to
            start &appshort; you will be required to provide your password.</para>
        <para>To start &appshort; from the menu system select <menuchoice>
                <guimenu>K Menu</guimenu>
                <guisubmenu>Settings</guisubmenu>
                <guimenuitem>Kynaptic (Package Manager)</guimenuitem>
            </menuchoice>. </para>
        <para>To start &appshort; from the command line:</para>
                <programlisting>
                sudo kynaptic
                </programlisting>
        <para>Both methods require that you enter your password. This will run &appshort; with
            root privileges which will be required in order to perform the requested operations. It
            is therefore advised that you use &appshort; with caution since improper usage could
            lead to the removal, deletion, or corruption of software packages that required in order
            to preserve system integrity.</para>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 id="get-started" status="review">
        <title>Getting Started</title>
        <para>On startup &appshort; will build the dependency tree for all installed software
            packages and then display the main window.</para>
        <figure id="main-window">
            <title>Main Window</title>
            <screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="figures/kynaptic.png" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                    <caption>Kynaptic: Main Window</caption>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot>
        </figure>
        <para>The main window is comprised of the following regions:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <xref linkend="kynaptic-menus" endterm="title-kynaptic-menus"/>
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <xref linkend="kynaptic-toolbar" endterm="title-kynaptic-toolbar"/>
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <xref linkend="kynaptic-selector" endterm="title-kynaptic-selector"/>
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <xref linkend="kynaptic-list" endterm="title-kynaptic-list"/>
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <xref linkend="kynaptic-status" endterm="title-kynaptic-status"/>
                </para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <sect2 id="kynaptic-menus" status="review">
            <title id="title-kynaptic-menus">Menu Bar</title>
            <para>The Menu Bar provides the following menus and options:</para>
            <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>File</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Import Marked Changes</emphasis>: </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Export Marked Changes</emphasis>: </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Refresh Package Information</emphasis>: </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Upgrade All Packages</emphasis>: </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Fix Broken Packages</emphasis>: </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Commit Marked Changes</emphasis>: </para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Edit</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Undo</emphasis>: </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Redo</emphasis>: </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Find</emphasis>: </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Filters</emphasis>: </para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
            </variablelist>
        </sect2>
        <sect2 id="kynaptic-toolbar" status="review">
            <title id="title-kynaptic-toolbar">Toolbar</title>
            <para>The toolbar provides the following actions from left to right:<variablelist>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>
                            <inlinemediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="figures/update.png" format="PNG"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </inlinemediaobject>
                        </term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Reload the list of packages from known software repositories.
                            </para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>
                            <inlinemediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="figures/distupgrade.png" format="PNG"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </inlinemediaobject>
                        </term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Upgrade all packages marked as upgradeable.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>
                            <inlinemediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="figures/proceed.png" format="PNG"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </inlinemediaobject>
                        </term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Commit all marked changes to the system.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                </variablelist>
            </para>
        </sect2>
        <sect2 id="kynaptic-selector" status="review">
            <title id="title-kynaptic-selector">Category Selector</title>
            <para>The left pane is known as the Category Selector. Comprised of a drop list and list
                box, it enables you to select categories containing predefined filters. When
                selected, filters serve to reduce the number of packages displayed in the <xref
                    linkend="kynaptic-list" endterm="title-kynaptic-list"/>. </para>
            <screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="figures/category-selector.png" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot>
            <para>The following categories are available:</para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <xref linkend="sections" endterm="title-sections"/>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <xref linkend="status" endterm="title-status"/>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <xref linkend="custom" endterm="title-custom"/>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <xref linkend="search-history" endterm="title-search-history"/>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
            <sect3 id="sections" status="review">
                <title id="title-sections">Sections</title>
                <para>Displays a list of filters pertaining to the package categories by which
                    software is organized. Select a filter to display a list of software within the
                    category.</para>
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="figures/kynaptic-sections.png" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <caption>Sections Filter List</caption>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
            </sect3>
            <sect3 id="status" status="review">
                <title id="title-status">Status</title>
                <para>Displays a list of filters arranged by possible package status'.</para>
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="figures/kynaptic-status.png" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <caption>Status Filter List</caption>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
                <para>The following status filters are provided:</para>
                <variablelist>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Installed</term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Displays the list of packages installed.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Installed (local or obsolete)</term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Displays the list of packages that are installed, but not included in the software repositories.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>New in repository</term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Displays a list of packages newly introduced to the software
                                repositories.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Not Installed</term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Displays a list of packages that are available but not
				installed, excluding packages that are new in the repository.
			    </para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Not installed (residual config)</term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Displays a list of packages that were installed (and have since been removed) and have left data or configuration files on the system.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                </variablelist>
            </sect3>
            <sect3 id="custom" status="review">
                <title id="title-custom">Custom</title>
                <para>Displays a list of filters providing custom criteria. This includes a set of
                    custom filter installed with &appshort; and any filters created by yourself.</para>
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="figures/kynaptic-custom.png" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <caption>Custom Filter List</caption>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
                <para>The following custom filters are provided:</para>
                <variablelist>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Broken</term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Displays a list of packages that are incorrectly installed or are
                                missing packages upon which they are dependent in order to function
                                correctly.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Marked Changes</term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Displays a list of packages for which the status has been changed
                                during the current &appshort; session.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Pkg with debconf</term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Displays a list of packages that can be configured through the Debian package configuration system (debconf).</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Search Filter</term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Displays a list of packages (results) from the last package search.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Upgradeable (upstream)</term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Displays a list of packages with a later upstream version available.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                </variablelist>
            </sect3>
            <sect3 id="search-history" status="review">
                <title id="title-search-history">Search history</title>
                <para>Displays a list of filters corresponding to the most recent search
                operations.</para>
            </sect3>
        </sect2>
        <sect2 id="kynaptic-list" status="review">
            <title id="title-kynaptic-list">Package List</title>
            <para>The right pane is known as the Package List. Package listings are dependent on the
                criteria defined by the filter selected in the <xref linkend="kynaptic-selector"
                    endterm="title-kynaptic-selector"/>.</para>
