    <sect1 id="software-management" status="review">
        <title>Software Management</title>
        <sect2 id="reload-source-list" status="review">
            <title>Reloading Source Lists</title>
            <para>When new software sources have been added to the <application>APT</application>
                software sources list the list of packages contained in the repository must be
                loaded. For already existing software sources &appshort; will already have a
                list of all software residing in a repository. This list is updated on a regular
                basis, normally once a day. Updates can be forced by clicking the
                <guibutton>Reload</guibutton> located on the toolbar or by selecting <menuchoice>
                    <guimenu>File</guimenu>
                    <guimenuitem>Refresh Package Information</guimenuitem>
                </menuchoice>.</para>
            <para>During the reload operation the status of the fetch operation for each software
                repository is shown by the <interface>Fetch Progress</interface> dialog.</para>
            <screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="figures/kynaptic-refresh.png" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot>
            <para>The <interface>Fetch Progress</interface> provides the following information about
                each fetch operation:</para>
            <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Progress</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>A progress bar displaying completion in percentage for each software
                            repository package list.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Status</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Three states are defined according to the following icon legend:</para>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <inlinemediaobject>
                                        <imageobject>
                                            <imagedata fileref="figures/yellow.png" format="PNG"/>
                                        </imageobject>
                                    </inlinemediaobject> = In Progress </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <inlinemediaobject>
                                        <imageobject>
                                            <imagedata fileref="figures/green.png" format="PNG"/>
                                        </imageobject>
                                    </inlinemediaobject> = Competed Successfully </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <inlinemediaobject>
                                        <imageobject>
                                            <imagedata fileref="figures/red.png" format="PNG"/>
                                        </imageobject>
                                    </inlinemediaobject> = Failed </para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Size</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>The size of the package list file reloaded in Kilobytes.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Description</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>The location (URL) and repository name from which the package list was
                            reloaded.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
            </variablelist>
        </sect2>
        <sect2 id="using-filters" status="review">
            <title>Using Filters</title>
            <para>The software package lists obtained from the software repositories can contain
                many thousands of records. Filters are used to query the package lists according to
                package status, packaging category, and user defined patterns.</para>
            <para>The following filters are already provided for you:</para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Search Filter</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Broken</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Marked Changes</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Pkg with Debconf</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Upgradable (Upstream)</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
            <para>Each of these filters can be modified by changing the properties of the <xref
                    linkend="status-tab" endterm="title-status-tab"/>, <xref linkend="section-tab"
                    endterm="title-section-tab"/>, and <xref linkend="patterns-tab"
                    endterm="title-patterns-tab"/> tabs.</para>
            <variablelist id="status-tab">
                <title id="title-status-tab">Status</title>
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="figures/kynaptic-filters-status.png" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Installation</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Check the Installation status conditions you want included in the
                            filter.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Marked Changes</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Check the Marked Changes status conditions you want included in the
                            filter.</para>
