        <sect2 id="commit-changes" status="review">
            <title>Committing Changes</title>
            <para>With &appshort;, none of the changes you have made will be applied onto your
                system until you commit the changes. To commit the changes, you may either select <menuchoice>
                    <guimenu>File</guimenu>
                    <guisubmenu>Commit Marked Changes...</guisubmenu>
                </menuchoice> or, more simply, click the third icon option in the toolbar. If you
                have selected to install particular packages, it will now firstly download all the
                requested packages, and it will then install them accordingly; at this point,
                packages that are selected for removal and upgrade will also be applied. </para>
            <para>After these changes have been committed, the package list will refresh to reflect
                all the changes made to the system.</para>
        </sect2>
